<subSubSection id="46F0657311277244F8A10E49869E244D" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0E5536F811277244F8A10E49869E244D" blockId="23.[151,1437,1611,1817]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA11277244F8A10E49841F2531" bold="true" box="[151,267,1611,1637]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Remarks.</emphasis>
BI (
<figureCitation id="96D12A7D11277244F9670E4984B92531" box="[337,429,1611,1637]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[572,1012,184,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-21@25.[572,1014,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12. Bayesian Inference tree (BI) reconstructed from a fragment of COI mitochondrial gene. Posterior probability values indicated on nodes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5744583" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5744583/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), ML (
<figureCitation id="96D12A7D11277244FA380E49877E2531" box="[526,618,1611,1637]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[575,1017,184,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@26.[570,1017,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 13. Maximum likelihood tree (ML) reconstructed from a fragment of COI mitochondrial gene. Ultrafast bootstrap support values indicated on nodes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5744585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5744585/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), the species-delimitation methods, and genetics distances analysis (Supplementary material 2) indicate that the sequences of this taxon cluster in a single well-differentiated, long branch, and to represent the sister species to 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B11277244FA960E91814225F9" authority="Adams &amp; Bernard, 1979" authorityName="Adams &amp; Bernard" authorityYear="1979" box="[672,1110,1683,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="navarrae">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA11277244FA960E91863B25F8" box="[672,815,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">M. navarrae</emphasis>
Adams &amp; Bernard, 1979
</taxonomicName>
, from the Serranía de Perija in northern 
<collectingCountry id="76FD766811277244F9290EB584852585" box="[287,401,1719,1745]" name="Colombia" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. Based these data we raise it to a specific rank. 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B11277244FBF30EB581802585" authorityName="Mahecha-J &amp; Florczyk &amp; Willmott &amp; Cerdeña &amp; Zubek &amp; Boyer &amp; Farfán &amp; Lachowska-Cierlik &amp; Pyrcz" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[965,1172,1719,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamasi" status="n. stat.">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA11277244FBF30EB581802585" box="[965,1172,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Manerebia lamasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA11277244FCAB0EB581E42585" bold="true" box="[1181,1264,1719,1745]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="27AD579111277244FCAB0EB581E42585" box="[1181,1264,1719,1745]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">n. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B11277244F9EE0ED987B425A0" box="[472,672,1755,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satura">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA11277244F9EE0ED987B425A0" box="[472,672,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">Manerebia satura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on similar male genitalia and wing colour patterns. 
<taxonomicName id="C9EA4D7B11277244FD1A0ED9808925A1" authorityName="Mahecha-J &amp; Florczyk &amp; Willmott &amp; Cerdeña &amp; Zubek &amp; Boyer &amp; Farfán &amp; Lachowska-Cierlik &amp; Pyrcz" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Pyrcz &amp; Willmott" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[1324,1437,1755,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Manerebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamasi" status="n. stat.">
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA11277244FD1A0ED9808925A1" box="[1324,1437,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">M. lamasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="3C9EEAEA11277244F8A10EFD85F3244D" bold="true" box="[151,231,1791,1817]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="27AD579111277244F8A10EFD85F3244D" box="[151,231,1791,1817]" pageId="23" pageNumber="224">n. stat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is known so far exclusively from the Cordillera del Condór.
</paragraph>
